snippet: The governor of Guerrero said that some of the 28 burned bodies found last week could not be identified as any of the 43 college students who had disappeared after clashing with the police.
abstract: Guerrero, Mexico, Gov Angel Aguirre says that some of the 28 burned bodies recovered from clandestine graves do not match those of 43 college students who disappeared after confrontation with police.
lead_paragraph: The governor of Guerrero said that some of the 28 burned bodies found last week could not be identified as any of the 43 college students who had disappeared after clashing with the police.

headline.main: Some Remains in Mexico Are Not of Missing Students
headline.print_headline: Some Remains in Mexico Are Not of Missing Students
